MacroLens

AI-powered food macronutrient tracker. Photograph a meal and get an instant breakdown of protein, carbohydrates, fat, and calories or enter your meal manually.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What it does

Detects food items in a photo using YOLOv8
Classifies each item using a Food-101 trained EfficientNetV2B0 model (81.9% Top-1 accuracy)
Estimates portion size using reference objects in the frame (forks, spoons, plates)
Looks up macronutrients from the USDA FoodData Central database
Lists ingredients per detected food
Suggests recipes via the Spoonacular API
Lets users log meals, track daily totals, and set macro goals
Allows reporting of wrong predictions

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Features

Photo upload - Drag and drop or file picker
Camera capture - Direct from device camera
Multi-food detection - Separate card per detected item
Portion slider - Adjust grams,macros recalculated in real time
AI portion estimate - Uses fork/spoon/plate as scale reference
Confidence score - Shown per detection
Ingredient list - Per detected food
Meal logging - Log individual items or all at once
Daily summary - Calories, protein, carbs, fat with goal bars
Manual entry - Add food manually with custom macro values
Search - USDA database search by food name
Recipes - Spoonacular recipe dropdown per detected food
Report prediction - Flag wrong AI predictions with your correction
Meal history - View and delete past logged meals

Authentication

Register with name, email, and password (6+ characters)
Passwords stored as SHA-256 hashes in users.json
Session-based login, all API routes require an active session
Meal history stored in browser localStorage - no cloud database required

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Technologies used

Backend - Python 3.11, Flask 3.0
Object detection - YOLOv8n (Ultralytics)
Food classification - TensorFlow 2.x, EfficientNetV2B0
Image processing - OpenCV 4.8
Nutrition data - USDA FoodData Central API
Recipe data - Spoonacular API
Frontend - HTML5, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
Auth - Flask sessions, SHA-256 hashing 
Storage - localStorage (meals), JSON file (users, reports)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Requirements

Python 3.11
pip packages in requirements.txt

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Setup 

Step 1: Extract the project
MacroLens/
    app.py
    reports.json
    README
    food101_efficientnetv2b0.keras
    food101_classes.json
    yolov8s.pt
    requirements.txt
    users.json
    templates/
        dashboard.html
        login.html

Step 2: Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 3: Add Spoonacular API key(optional)
Add your key from spoonacular.com/food-api in
SPOONACULAR_KEY = "YOUR_SPOONACULAR_API_KEY"

Step 4: Run the app
python app.py

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Model Files

food101_efficientnetv2b0.keras = Food-101 classifier (101 food classes)
food101_classes.json = Class label list
yolov8s.pt = YOLOv8 food object detector

If food101_efficientnetv2b0.keras is missing the app falls back to OpenCV colour analysis only.

